Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.70,0:00:09.71,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,The countless flowers,\Nenveloped in light…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.71,0:00:20.34,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,…gaze at tomorrow\Nwith unwavering eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.36,0:00:39.35,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Everyone wishes for me to be pure…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.35,0:00:46.81,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,…but what can I bring\Nwith me to the frayed skies?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.81,0:00:53.90,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,What I’ve made my own\Nby breaking off flowers in bloom…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.90,0:00:59.46,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,All such sinful things…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.46,0:01:06.91,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Why did I stop making\Npromises with the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.91,0:01:14.21,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Because even if I try\Nto run far from all the pain…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.21,0:01:20.89,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,…a cold wind rustles\Nmy hair… Don’t you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.89,0:01:28.04,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Where can I ever find the answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.43,0:01:40.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,Making another unauthorized\Nflight, Chor Tempest?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.70,0:01:41.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,Vura!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.04,0:01:47.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,Dux Guragief ordered us to go\Non a special training mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.01,0:01:51.28,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’re all busy with\Nregular duties, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.28,0:01:56.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we’re tired. Night patrol requires\Nfar more vigilance than day patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.41,0:01:58.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,And enemy encounters are likelier.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.96,0:02:02.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s easier to just float\Naround during the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.82,0:02:09.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,But your chor used to do\Nnothing but daytime patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.85,0:02:13.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,The night shift was always our job.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.07,0:02:15.94,Regular,,0,0,0,,But that’s not the case now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.94,0:02:19.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,The top chor on\NArcus Prima is now us, Rubor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.04,0:02:24.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,If you don’t like it,\Nthen prove you’re still worthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.03,0:02:27.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,Step aside. We’re exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.28,0:02:30.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,Everyone, let them pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.45,0:02:38.08,Regular,,0,0,0,,By the way, which Ri Majon?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.29,0:02:40.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,The Dandelion Ri Majon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.89,0:02:42.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,Dandelion?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.43,0:02:46.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,The ceremonial Ri Majon\Nused for diplomatic purposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.00,0:02:49.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why use\Nan old-fashioned Ri Majon like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.53,0:02:53.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,Vura!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.34,0:02:58.19,Regular,,0,0,0,,Help yourself to\Nthe leftover candy on my desk!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.84,0:03:01.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,Don’t wake me coming back!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.24,0:03:07.20,Titles,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.6}Over International Waters
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.54,0:03:31.10,Regular,,0,0,0,,Wow!\NLook how spotless you are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.84,0:03:37.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,These kids worked hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.82,0:03:41.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s quite an antique,\Nso they had a rough time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.38,0:03:43.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.25,0:03:46.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,My grandpa flew this\Nwhen he was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.36,0:03:50.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,Your grandfather\Nwas a Simoun sibylla too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.99,0:03:55.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,So after he went to the Spring and\Nstopped flying, he still treasured this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.42,0:04:25.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,They’re jealous that we always\Nused to be assigned night patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.24,0:04:30.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,When Chor Rubor used to run into\NNeviril, they’d just look on from afar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.50,0:04:32.74,Regular,,0,0,0,,Be proud of yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.74,0:04:39.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,As a member of Chor Tempest, I plan\Nto take this chor right back to the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.68,0:04:45.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right. As far as wanting to see\NTempest back on top, I’m with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.63,0:04:47.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess you’re right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.83,0:04:51.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,Since we won’t have to go to the\NSpring as long as we keep winning?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.89,0:04:54.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,Well, I can’t wait to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.09,0:04:57.22,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then what’s stopping you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.69,0:05:01.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,I want to go with\Nthe person I care about.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.03,0:05:05.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then when I emerge from\Nthe Spring, I’ll be a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.17,0:05:07.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,And she’ll be a woman…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.24,0:05:09.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,And you’ll consummate\Nthings then and there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.97,0:05:13.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,Quiet down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.51,0:05:16.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,Listen up, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.71,0:05:21.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,There are two obstacles\Nto becoming the best chor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.92,0:05:23.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,Unless we get two new members…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.29,0:05:26.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,…we won’t be able\Nto fly six Simouns at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.43,0:05:30.18,Regular,,0,0,0,,What’s the other thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.39,0:05:32.68,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.68,0:05:35.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,If Neviril and Aer flew as a pair…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.44,0:05:39.19,Regular,,0,0,0,,…it wouldn’t be a stretch\Nto see our chor back on top!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.54,0:05:41.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,Para-sama…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.14,0:05:44.60,Regular,,0,0,0,,…you’re giving up on Neviril?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.65,0:05:51.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,Let’s do it in front of the Arcus Prima!\NSo that the dux and Neviril can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.96,0:06:08.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,Morinas-san, higher!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.40,0:06:11.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,Am I not good enough\Nfor Sibylla Aurea?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.85,0:06:14.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,Morinas-san, please concentrate!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.52,0:06:15.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.05,0:06:18.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,You have to lead the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.38,0:06:19.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.56,0:06:21.85,Regular,,0,0,0,,So who’s this loved one?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.85,0:06:25.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,Floe, I’m hearing bad\Nthings about you lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.36,0:06:28.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,No way! It’s not true, is it, Alty?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.69,0:06:30.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,Of course it’s true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.36,0:06:32.06,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m so happy…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.06,0:06:35.16,Regular,,0,0,0,,Para-sama,\Nyou’re responding to my feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.16,0:06:37.30,Regular,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.30,0:06:39.87,Regular,,0,0,0,,I was sure you hated me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.87,0:06:41.77,Regular,,0,0,0,,Since the other day…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.77,0:06:42.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,Be specific!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.25,0:06:44.29,Regular,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.78,0:06:58.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,Arcus Niger? We’re not\Nsupposed to rendezvous till later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.35,0:06:59.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s the Niger. No mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.25,0:07:05.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,An emergency, perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.46,0:07:08.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m sure they’re just being\Nrushed by the higher-ups.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.59,0:07:11.57,Regular,,0,0,0,,You should summon\Nthe Tempest girls back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.50,0:07:17.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,Arcus Niger!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.98,0:07:18.83,Regular,,0,0,0,,Niger?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.83,0:07:22.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,They’re supposed to be west\Nof the great temple… Why…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.18,0:07:33.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,A Simile Simoun!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.93,0:07:35.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,A messenger?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.82,0:07:40.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,Even so…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.43,0:07:48.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,How lame is that pilot?\NMissing the cable like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.73,0:07:51.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,No, they’re avoiding it on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.95,0:07:55.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.87,0:07:58.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.38,0:08:01.54,Regular,,0,0,0,,Talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.29,0:08:07.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’re supposed to be Chor Tempest?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.76,0:09:01.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,Since the Plumbum highlands and\Nour nation share similar customs…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.25,0:09:04.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,…I didn’t think the decor\Nhere would offend you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.57,0:09:08.44,Regular,,0,0,0,,Let’s have\NTempus Spatium be scarce.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.44,0:09:12.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,That would undermine\Nour authority severely…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.53,0:09:15.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,The highlanders worship\Na deity named Animus.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.95,0:09:17.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,Historically speaking…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.82,0:09:22.31,Regular,,0,0,0,,…Animus and Tempus Spatium\Nare in fact the same god.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.79,0:09:26.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,The highlands and Kyuukoku\Ndo not acknowledge this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.63,0:09:29.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s best to avoid\Nunnecessary stimulation?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.73,0:09:32.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,For the sake of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.87,0:09:35.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,Tempus Spatium would\Nbe glad to be concealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.63,0:10:07.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,Peace conference?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.50,0:10:14.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right. It’s fair to say we’re battling\Nall our neighboring countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.34,0:10:16.97,Regular,,0,0,0,,Each one,\Nbecause of economic strife…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.97,0:10:20.22,Regular,,0,0,0,,They want the Simouns.\NNo matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.22,0:10:21.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.82,0:10:25.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,To be more precise,\Nthey’re after the helical motors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.89,0:10:29.73,Regular,,0,0,0,,Unearthed only from ruins,\Nthe wings that give Simouns flight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.73,0:10:35.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,But now the Plumbum highlands\Nhave come to broker a peace deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.63,0:10:39.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s been decided the first conference\Nwill be held in international waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.61,0:10:43.31,Regular,,0,0,0,,In utmost secrecy of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.31,0:10:46.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,So they’ll hold this conference\Non the Arcus Prima, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.11,0:10:51.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,Who cares about politics?\NAre we free to use the maju pool?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.50,0:10:54.67,Regular,,0,0,0,,I think they’ll say not\Nto act without permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.67,0:10:56.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey, it’s them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.65,0:10:59.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,The ones flying that Simile before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.43,0:11:03.01,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why are they\Nwandering around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.47,0:11:15.34,Regular,,0,0,0,,They’re headed this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.34,0:11:17.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,Why are they on our ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.71,0:11:21.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,The most obvious reason is\Nthat they’re new members…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.51,0:11:27.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey, I bet she’ll say something like,\N“Chor Tempest sure is a letdown.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.95,0:11:29.71,Regular,,0,0,0,,Right, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.22,0:11:36.67,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sorry for earlier,\Nmembers of Chor Tempest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.49,0:11:39.84,Regular,,0,0,0,,So it was you two after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.84,0:11:42.72,Regular,,0,0,0,,Still, you sure are a letdown.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.98,0:11:58.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,Is it that funny, my lady Roatreamon?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.02,0:12:04.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don’t blame you\Nfor not remembering.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.69,0:12:07.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,I just lived on your estate…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.93,0:12:11.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,…as the daughter of two\Nof your many servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.25,0:12:35.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,Come now, Mamina.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.59,0:12:44.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamina?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.43,0:12:49.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,I am honored that\Nyou remember me, my lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.14,0:12:57.58,Regular,,0,0,0,,As of today,\NI’ve been ordered to transfer…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.58,0:13:00.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,…from Arcus Niger’s\NChor Ignus to Chor Tempest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.98,0:13:05.05,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m Sibylla Mamina. I’m pleased\Nto make your acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.31,0:13:09.81,Regular,,0,0,0,,And I’m Yun.\NI’m also joining Chor Tempest.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.81,0:13:13.52,Regular,,0,0,0,,I have one thing to say. I despise war.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.26,0:13:15.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.09,0:13:22.87,Regular,,0,0,0,,Somebody!\NSomebody, please help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.87,0:13:25.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Aurea’s room…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.50,0:13:27.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,What’s this about Neviril?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.35,0:13:40.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.55,0:13:42.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,Paraietta…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.42,0:13:47.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,What’s going on?\NWhat do you think you’re doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.02,0:13:49.90,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Aurea sleeps\Nalone in her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.90,0:13:52.89,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s a privilege\Ngranted to her alone! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.89,0:13:55.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,Starting today,\Nshe’s sharing her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.77,0:13:57.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.00,0:13:59.86,Regular,,0,0,0,,Para, it’s been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.86,0:14:03.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes, it has, Vice Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.51,0:14:09.11,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril, I think this is a good way to\Nimmediately bond with your new pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.81,0:14:11.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,New pair?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.48,0:14:14.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then that’s my bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.49,0:14:17.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,A “new pair”…Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.99,0:14:20.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,Yes, I’m assigning Mamina.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.89,0:14:23.46,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.46,0:14:24.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.51,0:14:37.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,Pairs should be formed out of mutual\Nneed and according to the natural flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.35,0:14:42.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,You were once a sibylla, Father,\Nso you should be well aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.35,0:14:47.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril, in this day and age,\Nit doesn’t work that way anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.33,0:14:52.80,Regular,,0,0,0,,You must take this step now\Nor your name will be tarnished.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.80,0:14:56.39,Regular,,0,0,0,,I was an auriga,\Nbut if I can pair with you…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.39,0:14:59.04,Regular,,0,0,0,,…I’d be happy to fly as a sagitta.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.16,0:15:05.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamina is not from\Na family befitting a sibylla.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.47,0:15:10.98,Regular,,0,0,0,,But of all the great temple’s\Ncandidates, she scored the highest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.98,0:15:14.18,Regular,,0,0,0,,As far as the Wave Crest\Nand Tsunami Ri Majons…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.18,0:15:16.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,…I can pray better than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.08,0:15:19.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,Those are all highly dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.35,0:15:23.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,Which enable us to annihilate\Nmore enemies in one blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.36,0:15:26.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,All I want is for you to snap out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.50,0:15:28.69,Regular,,0,0,0,,Granted, a tragedy occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.69,0:15:35.12,Regular,,0,0,0,,But you shall overcome that and\Nregain your glory as Sibylla Aurea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.83,0:15:40.06,Regular,,0,0,0,,Meaning that your standing in\Nthe council will be safe, Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.47,0:15:44.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don’t understand what’s\Ngoing on in your head, Neviril.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.07,0:15:48.63,Regular,,0,0,0,,If you’re put off by battle,\Nthen you should go to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.18,0:15:51.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’ll surely become a lovely woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.41,0:15:57.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,But if you’re put off by the Spring and\Nrefuse to fly a Simoun, what then?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.38,0:16:00.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’re telling me\Nto give you an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.02,0:16:04.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’re old enough now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.15,0:16:06.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,Is Neviril coming back?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.89,0:16:09.78,Regular,,0,0,0,,Hey, Aer, you should\Npair with me after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.47,0:16:13.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,I like Neviril.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.78,0:16:18.16,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril really is popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.16,0:16:21.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,I think I’ll give up on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.78,0:16:23.62,Regular,,0,0,0,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.62,0:16:27.92,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’ll pair with someone. But even so,\NI’ll still despise what we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.92,0:16:30.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,If so, then just hurry on to the Spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.88,0:16:33.13,Regular,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.72,0:16:38.70,Regular,,0,0,0,,Already, many of my friends,\Ndespite being priestesses…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.70,0:16:43.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,…were sent to the battlefield since\Nthey could fly Simouns and perished.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.13,0:16:47.65,Regular,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t run away\Nfrom that just on my own!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.65,0:16:50.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,That reason sounds like a death wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.51,0:17:00.91,Regular,,0,0,0,,Paraietta.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.95,0:17:06.26,Regular,,0,0,0,,I always thought you and Neviril\Nwould fly as a pair one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.26,0:17:07.67,Regular,,0,0,0,,Vice Chancellor…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.10,0:17:11.17,Regular,,0,0,0,,No matter what, I will protect Neviril.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.43,0:17:55.42,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamina, I’m sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.42,0:17:56.59,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m still…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.28,0:18:05.64,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Aurea,\NI want you to be my pair…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.71,0:18:08.56,Regular,,0,0,0,,…body and soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.19,0:18:15.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,Sibylla Mamina, even if you\Ntake my body by force…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.09,0:18:18.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,…you will never be my pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.32,0:18:21.30,Regular,,0,0,0,,Neviril, try to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.30,0:18:25.66,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’ve got to pair up with you,\Nno matter what it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.42,0:18:49.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aer!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.43,0:18:57.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,You actually used that rope\Nto come through the window?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.73,0:19:00.82,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’re such a funny girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.64,0:19:09.09,Regular,,0,0,0,,All six Simouns will be needed\Nfor the Dandelion Ri Majon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.09,0:19:11.33,Regular,,0,0,0,,As Chor Tempest is now…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.33,0:19:15.38,Regular,,0,0,0,,We’ve already bolstered the ranks.\NIs that not enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.38,0:19:19.06,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s about whether it can be\Ndone with those new members.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.06,0:19:23.50,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s a prayer for a key event, the\Npeace conference with the highlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.50,0:19:26.35,Regular,,0,0,0,,We cannot risk failure of any kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.35,0:19:31.30,Regular,,0,0,0,,All I’m asking for is a Ri Majon\Nperformed by Chor Tempest.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.30,0:19:34.13,Regular,,0,0,0,,If you cannot comply\Nwith my request…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.90,0:19:36.36,Regular,,0,0,0,,What will you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.11,0:19:41.88,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don’t want my daughter\Nto suffer any more humiliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.88,0:19:44.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,I don’t want her to get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.80,0:20:05.57,Regular,,0,0,0,,Mamina! You want to challenge\Nme in the maju pool too?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.57,0:20:07.40,Regular,,0,0,0,,Challenge you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.87,0:20:10.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,To decide who’ll pair up with Neviril.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.14,0:20:12.02,Regular,,0,0,0,,It’s not a matter of challenging you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.52,0:20:20.03,Regular,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.41,0:20:22.93,Regular,,0,0,0,,As long as we have these outfits on…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.93,0:20:27.49,Regular,,0,0,0,,…the helical motors activate, allowing\Nus to float! But if it’s removed…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.49,0:20:28.67,Regular,,0,0,0,,You crazy?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.67,0:20:30.47,Regular,,0,0,0,,Say you’ll give up on her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.47,0:20:32.25,Regular,,0,0,0,,Cut it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.25,0:20:34.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,I’m going to pair with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.24,0:20:37.00,Regular,,0,0,0,,Same for me! But that’s up to her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.00,0:20:41.61,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’re of low birth and only made it\Nhere because you can fly a Simoun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.61,0:20:44.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,One such as you is unworthy of her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.21,0:20:46.51,Regular,,0,0,0,,The same goes for you too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.23,0:20:55.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.19,0:20:57.41,Regular,,0,0,0,,Aer!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.39,0:21:06.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,As long as such breaches\Nof conduct continue…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.53,0:21:10.24,Regular,,0,0,0,,…we can only conclude\NChor Tempest no longer functions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.24,0:21:12.76,Regular,,0,0,0,,By that, do you mean…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.27,0:21:18.07,Regular,,0,0,0,,Once the peace conference\Nis over, I want Chor Tempest…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.77,0:21:21.14,Regular,,0,0,0,,…to disband.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.68,0:21:23.55,Regular,,0,0,0,,Please wait, Vice Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.55,0:21:25.96,Regular,,0,0,0,,Then what of your daughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.96,0:21:27.53,Regular,,0,0,0,,That’s the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.53,0:21:33.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,I can’t leave her in this chor. She’ll go\Nto the Spring before she’s hurt further.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.43,0:21:36.48,Regular,,0,0,0,,U-Um, then what about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.26,0:21:39.15,Regular,,0,0,0,,You’ve disappointed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.12,0:22:47.83,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,It is played by my wounds…\Nthe song of prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.83,0:22:52.07,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Let it ring out over\Nthe grieving universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.07,0:22:59.11,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Can we change tomorrow?\NDon’t be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.11,0:23:06.67,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,I want to let you know\Nhow my heart’s overflowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.56,0:23:19.63,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,“I want to get closer to you.”\N“I want to feel your pulse.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.63,0:23:24.80,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,I was too defiant,\Nand I took the long way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.80,0:23:28.81,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,The blue moon is swaying silently.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.81,0:23:32.82,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,My true heart’s desire is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.82,0:23:38.14,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,I can’t reach you.\NMy tears of pain trickle down.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.65,0:23:44.22,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Soar away into the sky, song of prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.22,0:23:47.66,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Carrying my love that came too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.66,0:23:53.33,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,What can I do to change tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.33,0:23:59.70,Lyrics bottom,,0,0,0,,Just hold on to “now” the way it is…
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.92,0:24:06.59,Titles,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.6}To Be Continued
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.71,0:24:08.21,Regular,,0,0,0,,The highland priestess named Anglas…
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.21,0:24:12.43,Regular,,0,0,0,,…will be staying with\NChor Tempest for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.47,0:24:16.95,Regular,,0,0,0,,Next time on Simoun…
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.95,0:24:18.32,Regular,,0,0,0,,Prayer.
